  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA211-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu varaivu nīṭa orutalai āṟṟāḷām eṉṟa tōḻi ciṟaippuṟamākat taṉṉuḷḷē colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">What [SHE] said to her own heart when the confidante was behind the fence who said that she was unable to bear it one one side when the marriage was delayed.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA211">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            yārkkunon turaikkō yāṉē yūrkaṭa</l>
<l>            lōtañ ceṉṟa vuppuṭaic ceṟuviṟ</l>
<l>            koṭuṅkaḻi maruṅki ṉiraivēṭ ṭeḻunta</l>
<l>            karuṅkāṟ kurukiṉ kōḷuyntu pōkiya</l>
<l>            muṭaṅkupuṟa viṟaviṉ mōvā yēṟṟai </l>
<l>            yeṟitirai tokutta vekkar neṭuṅkōṭṭut</l>
<l>            tuṟukaṟ ṟalaiya tōṭupoti tāḻai</l>
<l>            vaṇṭupaṭu vāṉpōtu verūun</l>
<l>            tuṟaikeḻu koṇkaṉ ṟuṟantaṉa ṉeṉavē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>
<choice>
    <seg>To whom shall I speak achingly</seg>
    <seg>Aching for whom shall I speak<note place="foot">This second possible nuance might well be calculated: a play with two topoi, on the one hand HER loneliness in a secret that cannot be shared, on the other hand the doubt about the character of HIM who is absent.</note></seg>
</choice>
</l>
<l>“he has abandoned [me], the man from the sea with ghats,</l>
<l rend="indent">where the bearded male<note place="foot">Note here <term xml:lang="ta">ēṟṟai</term>, elsewhere applied to male tigers and the like, with reference to prawn (or, if this might be used as an argument to show that <term xml:lang="ta">iṟavu</term> cannot mean "prawn", to a fish).</note> of the hunch-backed prawn,</l>
<l rend="indent">escaped [and] gone from the hold of the black-legged heron</l>
<l rend="indent2">that had risen to hunt for prey on the side of the curved</l>
<l rend="indent2">backwaters by the salt fields from which the flood had gone</l>
<l rend="indent2">with the creeping sea,</l>
<l rend="indent">is frightened by the sky buds frequented by bees</l>
<l rend="indent2">of the Tāḻai trees with bundles of petals(?) exalted on thick stones</l>
<l rend="indent3">in the long mounts of sand gathered by the dashing waves”?</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
